                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Deputies’ Report</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council heard and approved the report of the 123rd meeting of the Deputies,
                    made by the Acting Chairman.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Withdrawal of Allied Troops</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Article 21, Draft Treaty with Roumania</hi>,<note n="79"
                        xml:id="d367fn79">
                        <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_68">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            68</ref>.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">and Article 20, Draft Treaty with Hungary</hi>).<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d367fn80">This article is identical, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, to article 21 of the Draft Rumanian Treaty; for text, see
                            <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_68">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>The U.K. Delegation did not press for a discussion of new questions in connection
                    with these Articles and it was <hi rend="italic">decided</hi> that these agreed
                    Articles would be retained unchanged in the texts of the Draft Treaties with
                    Roumania and Hungary.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Date of Withdrawal of Allied Troops From
                        the Free Territory of Trieste</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The report of the Military Experts on the withdrawal of troops from the Free
                    Territory of Trieste was <hi rend="italic">approved</hi> (<gloss
                        target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss> 34).<note n="81" xml:id="d367fn81"
                        >For the text of this short document, see footnote 46, <ref
                            target="#pg_1323">p. 1323</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="1377" n="1353" xml:id="pg_1353"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Regime of the Danube</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Consideration of the proposal of the U.S.S.R. Delegation on the Danube and the
                    amendments tabled thereon was <hi rend="italic">deferred.</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">V. <hi rend="italic">Article 16 Bis. Paragraph 10</hi>(<hi
                        rend="italic">b</hi>). <hi rend="italic">Citizenship</hi>
                    <note n="82" xml:id="d367fn82">For the previous draft of this item, see <gloss
                            target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>28, November 25, 1946, <ref
                            target="#pg_1278">p. 1278</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The wording of paragraph 10(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>), Citizenship, was approved
                    as follows (the last paragraph is the proposed U.S. addition mentioned at the
                    123rd meeting of the Deputies; see Record of Decisions, Minute IV, (<hi
                        rend="italic">c</hi>)): <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The conditions for the acquisition of citizenship by persons not
                            qualifying for original citizenship shall be determined by the
                            Constituent Assembly of the Free Territory and embodied in the
                            Constitution.</p>
                        <p>“Such conditions shall, however, exclude the acquisition of citizenship
                            by members of the former Italian Fascist Police (O.V.R.A.), who have not
                            been exonerated by the competent authorities, including the Allied
                            Military Authorities, who were responsible for the administration of the
                            area.</p>
                        <p>“No person who has acquired the citizenship of the Free Territory shall
                            be deprived of his civic or political rights except as judicial
                            punshment for the infraction of the penal laws of the Territory.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">VI. <hi rend="italic">Italian Reparations for Yugoslavia,
                        Greece, Albania and Ethiopia and Bulgarian Reparations for Yugoslavia and
                        Greece</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this question was deferred.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">VII. <hi rend="italic">Compensation for Damages to United
                        Nations’ Property in Italy, Roumania, Bulgaria, Hungary and Finland</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this question was <hi rend="italic"
                        >deferred.</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">VIII. <hi rend="italic">Roumanian Treaty, Article 24, Paragraphs
                        4</hi>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>) <hi rend="italic">and</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">e</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Nondiscrimination Against United
                        Nations Nationals</hi>.<note n="83" xml:id="d367fn83">The items under
                        reference were included in the Record of Recommendations of the Peace
                        Conference on the Draft Peace Treaty with Rumania, <ref
                            target="frus1946v04#pg_925">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            925</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this question was <hi rend="italic"
                        >deferred</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IX. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Saturday, November 30, 1946, at 4:00 p.m.</p>
